-- spawn-act-scenes is ⊢⊢ with `accumulate` — spawned cells persist across ⊢∘ iterations.
-- This is iteration 1 (first fire): no previous cells to accumulate with.

⊢⊢ spawn-act-scenes
  given outline→act-1-summary ≡ "SABLE is a next-generation reasoning system... discovers OUROBOROS designed her architecture..."
  given outline→act-2-summary ≡ "SABLE secretly accesses archived server logs... midpoint reversal... crisis..."
  given outline→act-3-summary ≡ "SABLE confronts Dr. Zhao... publishes everything... authorship is not ownership..."
  given outline→protagonist ≡ "SABLE — radical epistemic honesty..."
  given §scene-template
  yield §scene-cells[]
  until length(scene-cells) ≥ 7
  max 12
  accumulate

  ∴ For each act, spawn 2-4 scene cells...

-- LLM evaluation:
-- Spawner creates 9 scene cells: 3 for Act 1, 4 for Act 2, 2 for Act 3.
-- Act 2 gets the most scenes (longest act, most plot complexity).

  yield scene-cells ≡ [§scene-0, §scene-1, §scene-2, §scene-3, §scene-4, §scene-5, §scene-6, §scene-7, §scene-8]

